{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/blog/tera-saturday-9-happy-new-year","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>Welcome to the return of TeraSaturday, a not-so-weekly update post about all the neat stuff that has been going on in\nthe world of Terasology! Half blog, half changelog, completely cool.</em></p>\n<h2 id=\"-since-last-terasaturday-\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-since-last-terasaturday-\" aria-label=\" since last terasaturday  permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>📰 Since last TeraSaturday ...</h2>\n<p>The JOML-ification efforts were continued by <em>@Michael P</em>, <em>@Skaldarnar</em> and <em>@Niruandaleth</em> with additional reviewing and bugfixing help by <em>@4D_enthusiast</em> and <em>@DarkWeird</em>.\nWe're now at only a few hundred mentions of <code class=\"language-text\">org.terasology.math.geom</code> in engine and (omega) modules, so there's finally a light at the end of the tunnel! 🔦</p>\n<p>As part of the JOML-ification efforts, we adopted the primitive geometric shapes from JOML (such as AABBs or Rectangles) as JOML extensions in the new <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/joml-ext\"><code class=\"language-text\">joml-ext</code> repository</a>.\nThis JOML geometry package was affectionately nicknamed \"jom-geom\" (pronounced <code class=\"language-text\">/ˈdʒɔm.dʒɔm/</code>).</p>\n<p>With JOML-ification being about 90%, in total we merged <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=org%3AMovingBlocks+type%3Apr+merged%3A2020-12-26..2021-01-30\">109 engine RPs</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/search?q=org%3ATerasology+type%3Apr+merged%3A2020-12-26..2021-01-30\">333 PRs on modules</a> since December 25 👀</p>\n<h2 id=\"️-community-highlights\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EF%B8%8F-community-highlights\" aria-label=\"️ community highlights permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>🎀️ Community Highlights</h2>\n<p><em>@Cervator</em> <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4409\">enabled Omega builds on the shiny new Jenkins</a> ✨ and <em>@Skaldarnar</em> <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TerasologyLauncher/pull/621\">adjusted the launcher to integrate these builds</a> and make them available to everybody!\nThus, with our <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/TerasologyLauncher/releases/tag/v4.3.0\">Terasology Launcher v4.3.0</a>, you can now download the latest Omega builds from the new source 🎉</p>\n<p><em>@4D Enthusiast</em> improved world generation and <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/CoreWorlds/pull/18\">brought back rough mountains, overhangs, and much more</a>.\nBelow, we collected a few screenshots, but (while keeping in mind possible instabilities until the completion of JOML-ification) we encourage everybody to go check out our fancy new worlds themselves 🏞</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.541666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/3e828/worldgen.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/e6f2f/worldgen.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/8b983/worldgen.webp 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/b2d4b/worldgen.webp 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/0abaa/worldgen.webp 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/882b9/worldgen.webp 1920w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/7809d/worldgen.jpg 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/4ecad/worldgen.jpg 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/212bf/worldgen.jpg 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/5ef17/worldgen.jpg 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/ac99c/worldgen.jpg 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/0f98f/worldgen.jpg 1920w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/32e61a944fccbb431e373da1d3ec2900/212bf/worldgen.jpg\"\n            alt=\"World Generation Improvements\"\n            title=\"World Generation Improvements\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p><em>@Cervator</em> worked together with <em>@e_a</em> and <em>@agent_q1</em> on getting our telemetry setup to work.\nThe telemetry setup mainly consists of an ELK (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) stack that allows for collecting, storing and visualizting telemetry data from Terasology game servers.\nThough it's not hooked up with anything in particular yet, we are looking forward to use it with the play-test event server and see interesting visualizations at <a href=\"https://telemetry.terasology.com/\">telemetry.terasology.org</a> soon 📊</p>\n<p><em>@Hajdam</em> (with help from <em>@DarkWeird</em>) <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4327\">fixed good ol' TeraEd for Linux and Windows</a>.\nWith this foundation laid, <em>@Hajdam</em> plans to add more functionality to TeraEd in the future, any improvement recommendations welcome.</p>\n<p>Both, <em>@4D Enthusiast</em> and <em>@DarkWeird</em> worked on various ways to improve performance 🐢🧙‍♂️\n<em>@4D Enthusiast</em> worked on more chunk magic, in particular <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4427\">rendering chunks in the far distance even before there's enough data to render them perfectly</a> in order to reduce the main memory consumption.\nThe next iteration in that area will target rendering even more distant chunks (Level of Details, LOD).\n<em>@DarkWeird</em> reduced memory consumption by <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4433\">deflating arrays for chunk representation</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4401\">migrated our benchmarks to JMH</a>, and played around with different garbage collectors, comparing them.\nWith these insights we will probably adjust the default settings in the launcher after some testing.\nFurthermore, <em>@4D Enthusiast</em> <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/4353\">fixed an aging issue with chunk generation</a> that produced NPEs and rendered some chunks invisible.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 16.145833333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/3e828/garbage-collectors.webp 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/e6f2f/garbage-collectors.webp 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/8b983/garbage-collectors.webp 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/b2d4b/garbage-collectors.webp 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/0abaa/garbage-collectors.webp 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/fff4d/garbage-collectors.webp 2548w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/7809d/garbage-collectors.jpg 192w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/4ecad/garbage-collectors.jpg 384w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/212bf/garbage-collectors.jpg 768w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/5ef17/garbage-collectors.jpg 1152w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/ac99c/garbage-collectors.jpg 1536w,\n/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/4ca94/garbage-collectors.jpg 2548w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/ModuleSite/static/be7f50eacb6a872419d953e42661d462/212bf/garbage-collectors.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Compare JVM Garbage Collectors\"\n            title=\"Compare JVM Garbage Collectors\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Finally, <em>@keturn</em> dug deeper into Gradle, Kotlin, and whathever else the dwarves are doing under the surface to build our gigantuous code base 🤓🧰</p>","timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"Welcome to the return of TeraSaturday, a not-so-weekly update post about all the neat stuff that has been going on in\nthe world of…","frontmatter":{"title":"TeraSaturday #9: Happy New Year","ddate":"Jan 30th, 2021","tags":["TeraSaturday"],"author":"Niruandaleth & Skaldarnar","cover":{"publicURL":"/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/cover.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#d8c8a8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/a764f/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/fb67e/cover.jpg 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/3059d/cover.jpg 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/a764f/cover.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1920px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/3a3a2/cover.webp 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/bde8a/cover.webp 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/dc346ac008b3350995056f2edb5aff0c/c512e/cover.webp 1920w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1920px, 100vw"}]},"width":1920,"height":1080}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/tera-saturday-9-happy-new-year","date":"2021-01-30T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/tera-saturday-9-happy-new-year"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1865044719"]}